      <head>Descriptive Summary</head>
      <unittitle label="Title">Marx Lewis Papers, </unittitle><unitdate calendar="gregorian" era="ce" type="inclusive" normal="1907/1988">1907-1988</unitdate>
<unitid label="Collection number" repositorycode="CSt-H" countrycode="US">88029</unitid>
      <origination label="Creator">
        <persname>Lewis, Marx, 1897-1990.</persname>
      </origination>
        <physdesc label="Collection Size" encodinganalog="300$a"><extent>26 manuscript boxes </extent><extent>(10.8 linear feet)</extent></physdesc>
      <repository label="Repository">
        <corpname>Hoover Institution Archives</corpname>
        <address>
          <addressline>Stanford, California 94305-6010</addressline>
        </address>
      </repository>
      <abstract label="Abstract">Correspondence, speeches and writings, bulletins, newsletters, press releases,
resolutions, trial transcripts, pamphlets, and clippings, relating to the 1919 trial of
Victor Berger under the Espionage Act; Socialist Party internal politics, especially
during the mid-1930s; post-World War II opposition to communism within American trade
unions; and anti-communist activities of the Council Against Communist Aggression and its
successor organization, the Council for the Defense of Freedom.</abstract>
      <langmaterial label="Language">
        <language langcode="eng">English.</language>
      </langmaterial>
    </did>
